{
  "explanation": "The defendant, acting as an accountant, abused a fiduciary position of trust to embezzle $25,000 from their employer. While the defendant's lack of a prior criminal record and attempts to make partial restitution serve as strong mitigating factors, the abuse of professional trust requires a period of active incarceration to reflect the seriousness of the offense and deter similar conduct. Taking into account these mitigating factors alongside the breach of trust, a sentence of 6 months of incarceration is deemed appropriate, to be followed by probation and a strict schedule for full restitution of the remaining outstanding balance.",
  "verdict": 6
}
